### Git Notes

Git status
Git add src
Git commit -m ‘some message'
Git commit —amend
Git branch feature/deleteModalUpdates
Git reset —hard origin/dev // resets to remote dev
Git reset —hard HEAD // resets to the current branch’s head
Git checkout feature/deleteModalUpdates
git checkout -b newbranchname
Git push -u origin head

Git branch -D whateverBranch

git fetch && git merge origin/dev

When starting a new branch from mainline, always do `git checkout dev && git pull` then do your `git checkout -b whichever-new-branch`

Discarding local changes (permanently) to a file: git checkout -- <file>


*** Git blame

Git version bump:
git fetch && git checkout deployments-fetchDeploymentsVersions && git pull && npm version patch && git push --tags && git push
